# Next.js 14 (App Router) Rules

## Routing
- Use App Router exclusively — all routes under `app/`
- Page files: `app/<route>/page.tsx`
- Layout files: `app/<route>/layout.tsx`
- API routes: `app/api/<route>/route.ts` with named exports (`GET`, `POST`, etc.)
- Never use `pages/` directory or `getServerSideProps`/`getStaticProps`

## Server vs Client Components
- Default to Server Components
- Add `"use client"` only for interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs
- Never import server-only code (Prisma, env secrets) in Client Components
- Use `server-only` package to enforce boundaries where critical

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled — avoid `any`, use `unknown` and narrow
- Prefer `type` over `interface`
- Use `satisfies` for type-safe object literals

## Prisma
- Import client from `lib/prisma.ts` only — it's a singleton
- Database queries only in Server Components, Route Handlers, or Server Actions
- Use `prisma.$transaction()` for atomic operations
- Use `include` for related data rather than multiple queries

## Validation
- Use `zod` at all API and form boundaries
- Define schemas close to where they're used
